```rust
//! # Theme System
//!
//! The lipgloss theme system provides a flexible way to manage colors
//! across your terminal application. It supports:
//!
//! - **Built-in presets**: Popular color schemes like Dracula, Nord, and Catppuccin
//! - **Custom themes**: Define your own color palette with semantic slots
//! - **Runtime switching**: Change themes dynamically without restarting
//! - **Auto-updating styles**: ThemedStyle automatically reflects theme changes
//! - **Serialization**: Save and load themes from JSON/TOML files
//!
//! ## Quick Start
//!
//! ```rust
//! use lipgloss::{Style, ThemePreset, ColorSlot};
//!
//! // Use a built-in preset
//! let theme = ThemePreset::Dracula.to_theme();
//!
//! // Create themed styles
//! let title = Style::from_theme(&theme, ColorSlot::Primary)
//!     .bold(true);
//!
//! let error = Style::from_theme(&theme, ColorSlot::Error);
//!
//! println!("{}", title.render("Welcome!"));
//! println!("{}", error.render("Something went wrong"));
//! ```
//!
//! ## Semantic Color Slots
//!
//! Themes use semantic color slots rather than hardcoded colors:
//!
//! | Slot | Purpose |
//! |------|---------|
//! | `Background` | Main background color |
//! | `Foreground` | Default text color |
//! | `Primary` | Primary accent (buttons, links) |
//! | `Secondary` | Secondary accent |
//! | `Success` | Success messages (green) |
//! | `Warning` | Warning messages (yellow/orange) |
//! | `Error` | Error messages (red) |
//! | `Muted` | De-emphasized text |
//! | `Border` | UI borders and dividers |
//!
//! ## Runtime Theme Switching
//!
//! ```rust
//! use lipgloss::{ThemeContext, ThemePreset};
//!
//! let ctx = ThemeContext::from_preset(ThemePreset::Dark);
//!
//! // Later, switch themes
//! ctx.set_preset(ThemePreset::Nord);
//! ```

/// A semantic color slot within a theme.
///
/// Color slots represent the *purpose* of a color rather than a specific
/// color value. This allows styles to automatically adapt when the theme
/// changes.
///
/// # Example
///
/// ```rust
/// use lipgloss::{Theme, ColorSlot};
///
/// let theme = ThemePreset::Dracula.to_theme();
/// let primary_color = theme.get(ColorSlot::Primary); // Returns purple (#bd93f9)
///
/// // Same code with different theme gives different color
/// let theme = ThemePreset::Nord.to_theme();
/// let primary_color = theme.get(ColorSlot::Primary); // Returns cyan (#88c0d0)
/// ```
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Hash)]
